$ include/linux/input.h

? Declarations of interesting functions in `include/linux/input.h` are, imho:
  

{ struct input_value #linux-input_value

  The `input_value` struct represents an *input value*:
code {
struct input_value {
  __u16 type;
  __u16 code;
  __s32 value;
}
code }

  Compare with → Linux/kernel/source/include/uapi/linux/input_h#linux-input_event[`struct input_event`] found in `→ Linux/kernel/source/include/uapi/linux/input_h`.

}
{ struct input_dev

  The `input_dev` struct represents an *input device*.

}

